SUMMARY:Weekend @Long Beach for the Razor Clam Festival
DESCRIPTION:The Portland Hiking Meetup Group\n**First things first\, this is a paid event\, it is $80 per person for the whole weekend. You first go on the waitlist. You will then need to contact me for payment details to get moved to the going list.**\n\nHi folks. I have rented a house in Long Beach\, WA for the weekend of the Razor Clam Festival. This is a large house\, close to town where all the festivities will be taking place. There are a ton of things to do in the area\, aside from the festival. This includes hiking in a national wildlife preserve\, visiting one of several museums\, checking out the historic town of Oysterville or seeing some cranberry bogs. There is also my favorite activity\, driving on the beach!! So fun.\n\nThe festival will have many activities going on\, including live music\, and of course lots of good food to enjoy. Go here for some details:\n[Long Beach Razor Clam Festival – Long Beach Washington Razor Clam Festival](https://www.longbeachrazorclamfestival.com/)\n\nThe check in time for the house is 4pm. I would advise getting to town earlier\, as the festival is happening all day on Friday\, as well as Saturday. The house has several areas to sleep and hang out\, full kitchen etc. Bring whatever you need for the weekend\, we will probably mostly be eating out\, but bring any food and beverages you like\, as you may prefer to cook some meals on your own. And don't forget games. Many people like games in the evenings which can be a lot of fun.\n\nI always encourage carpooling for many reasons\, so try to be a driver or a rider with some others. If you have any questions\, then please ask. I'm looking forward to a fun time!
